==================================================
POST-MVP EXPANSION LAYER
PARTNERSHIP, EXPERIENCE & MATURITY INTELLIGENCE ENGINE
==================================================

PURPOSE:
The platform must understand that many contracts are not won by a single company possessing every capability internally.

Government contracting frequently operates through:
- subcontracting
- OEM partnerships
- supplier relationships
- teaming agreements
- staffing partnerships
- joint ventures

The platform should help determine:
- what gaps are solvable
- what gaps are critical
- what partnerships may enable execution
- what opportunities should be avoided entirely

==================================================
CORE PHILOSOPHY
==================================================

The platform should NOT assume:
“If the user lacks one capability, the opportunity is impossible.”

Instead, the system should determine:
- whether missing capabilities are solvable
- whether partnerships can close capability gaps
- whether operational maturity is sufficient
- whether opportunity risk is realistic

==================================================
IMPORTANT SYSTEM RULE
==================================================

The platform should distinguish between:

1. SOLVABLE CAPABILITY GAPS
and

2. CRITICAL / DISQUALIFYING GAPS

This distinction is foundational to opportunity intelligence.

==================================================
SOLVABLE CAPABILITY GAPS
==================================================

These are gaps that can potentially be resolved through:
- subcontractors
- suppliers
- OEM partnerships
- staffing partners
- teaming agreements
- fulfillment partners

EXAMPLES:
- lumber sourcing
- logistics support
- cloud infrastructure
- delivery providers
- OEM reseller authorization
- staffing augmentation
- manufacturing partners

==================================================
CRITICAL / DISQUALIFYING GAPS
==================================================

These are gaps that are difficult or impossible to overcome through simple partnerships.

EXAMPLES:
- mandatory past performance
- required facility clearance
- required security clearance
- required federal contract vehicle
- mandatory certifications
- mandatory operational history
- mandatory overseas capability
- highly specialized defense experience

==================================================
GAP SEVERITY ENGINE
==================================================

PURPOSE:
Classify every detected capability gap.

OUTPUT TYPES:
- Solvable
- Moderate Risk
- Critical
- Disqualifying

