==================================================
PARTNERSHIP INTELLIGENCE ENGINE
==================================================

PURPOSE:
Determine whether strategic partnerships could make an opportunity executable.

POSSIBLE PARTNERSHIP TYPES:
- OEM authorization partner
- subcontractor
- staffing agency
- logistics provider
- cloud provider
- manufacturing partner
- compliance partner
- defense prime
- systems integrator

==================================================
OEM & AUTHORIZED RESELLER LOGIC
==================================================

The platform should detect:
- brand name requirements
- OEM restrictions
- authorized reseller requirements
- supply chain restrictions
- anti-gray-market restrictions

The system should determine:
- whether the user already qualifies
- whether OEM authorization is realistically obtainable
- whether reseller partnership is possible

==================================================
SUPPLY CHAIN INTELLIGENCE
==================================================

The platform should identify contracts requiring:
- authorized sourcing
- certified hardware channels
- supply chain validation
- origin verification
- delivery compliance

EXAMPLES:
- enterprise GPU hardware
- defense electronics
- telecommunications systems
- restricted hardware vendors

==================================================
COMPANY MATURITY ENGINE
==================================================

PURPOSE:
Evaluate company maturity against contract maturity.

The platform should analyze:
- years in business
- federal contract history
- past performance size
- team size
- staffing capacity
- operational scale
- certifications
- clearances
- revenue range
- supplier relationships

==================================================
IMPORTANT SYSTEM RULE
==================================================

The platform should aggressively suppress:
- unrealistic opportunities
- contracts beyond operational maturity
- impossible qualification scenarios
- dangerous overextension risks

==================================================
EXPERIENCE PROGRESSION MODEL
==================================================

The system should guide users through realistic growth stages.

==================================================
STAGE 1
==================================================

ENTRY-LEVEL GOVCON

Examples:
- simple RFQs
- commodity fulfillment
- small procurement
- local delivery
- subcontract roles
- small prototypes
- low-risk service contracts

==================================================
STAGE 2
==================================================

MID-TIER CONTRACTING

Examples:
- technical service contracts
- moderate software projects
- small prime contracts
- staffing augmentation
- regional fulfillment
- research/prototype work

==================================================
STAGE 3
==================================================

ADVANCED GOVCON

Examples:
- large primes
- IDIQ contracts
- major staffing contracts
- defense systems
- overseas operations
- multi-year contracts
- enterprise modernization

==================================================
OPPORTUNITY SUPPRESSION LOGIC
==================================================

EXAMPLE RULES:

IF:
- company_past_performance = 0
- contract_value > $350,000
- mandatory_past_performance = true

THEN:
- suppress by default

==================================================
ADDITIONAL SUPPRESSION EXAMPLES
==================================================

SUPPRESS IF:
- mandatory clearance missing
- staffing scale unrealistic
- overseas capability absent
- required certifications unavailable
- operational burden exceeds maturity
- required facility clearance missing

==================================================
PARTNERSHIP FEASIBILITY ANALYSIS
==================================================

The platform should determine:
“Can partnerships realistically close this gap?”

EXAMPLES:
- YES → OEM authorization partnership
- YES → logistics subcontractor
- YES → staffing partner
- NO → mandatory classified facility clearance
- NO → highly specialized past performance requirement

==================================================
RECOMMENDED EXECUTION STRATEGIES
==================================================

The platform should classify opportunities into:
- Prime Contractor
- Subcontractor
- Teaming Opportunity
- Supplier Fulfillment
- OEM Partnership
- Staffing Partnership
- Avoid Opportunity

